### Human User Authentication Policy

{%- if human_auth_methods == "SAML Only (SSO required)" %}
- Authentication: SAML only
- Users must use SSO via {{ identity_provider }}
- MFA handled by Identity Provider
{%- elif human_auth_methods == "SAML or Password with MFA" %}
- Authentication: SAML or Password
- MFA: {{ mfa_method }} (for password logins)
- Users can choose SSO or password + MFA
{%- else %}
- Authentication: Password only
- MFA: {{ mfa_method }} (required)
- Users authenticate directly with Snowflake
{%- endif %}

### Service Account Authentication Policy

{%- if service_auth_methods == "OAuth Only" %}
- Authentication: OAuth only
- Requires OAuth integration
{%- elif service_auth_methods == "Key Pair Only" %}
- Authentication: Key-pair only
- No passwords to manage
- Most secure for automated access
{%- elif service_auth_methods == "OAuth or Key Pair" %}
- Authentication: OAuth or key-pair
- Flexibility for different integration types
{%- else %}
- Authentication: OAuth, key-pair, or PAT
- Maximum flexibility including personal access tokens
{%- endif %}

### Policy Application

{%- if apply_auth_policies_account_level == "Yes - Apply default policy to all users" %}
**Account-Level Enforcement: Enabled**
- The human user authentication policy applies to all users by default
- Break-glass accounts must have their own policy explicitly assigned
- Service accounts should have the service policy explicitly assigned
{%- else %}
**Account-Level Enforcement: Disabled**
- Policies are created but not applied at account level
- Assign policies to users as needed
- Consider phased rollout starting with admin users
{%- endif %}

### Important Notes

- Break-glass accounts have their own policy allowing password-only access
- Admin users should use the human authentication policy
- Apply service policy only to designated service accounts